00:05:52.440 --> 00:05:56.040
And the planned extension to Watford Junction was cancelled by Sadiq Khan in 2016.

00:05:56.480 --> 00:05:59.420
Would these things have happened if the locals had a chance to vote the mayor out?

00:06:00.040 --> 00:06:01.520
Does anything need to be done about this?

00:06:01.800 --> 00:06:05.920
After all, the border of what counts as London has changed time and time again since the Romans.

00:06:06.220 --> 00:06:11.000
So now, 50-something years since Greater London was invented, is it time to look at those borders again?

00:06:11.660 --> 00:06:14.920
London may have stopped physically sprawling outwards when the Green Belt was introduced

00:06:14.960 --> 00:06:18.540
in the 30s, but the capital's influence is still very expanding indeed.

00:06:19.120 --> 00:06:23.080
People are now commuting into London from further than ever before as they seek cheaper housing.

00:06:23.460 --> 00:06:26.380
Shouldn't these people have a say in how the city they depend on is run?

00:06:26.760 --> 00:06:31.120
And then there's the six airports, only two of which are in Greater London. Is it about time that changed?

00:06:31.720 --> 00:06:33.420
In the end, it's not really important.

00:06:33.720 --> 00:06:37.200
In a world where borders are worryingly starting to matter more than ever before,

00:06:37.320 --> 00:06:40.040
this one that we've been discussing is thankfully quite a benign one.

00:06:40.560 --> 00:06:44.160
It's not as if Greater London is a city state that you need a passport to get into...

00:06:45.040 --> 00:06:45.760
yet.

00:06:46.260 --> 00:06:49.600
So for now, depending on how you live, work, shop and feel,

00:06:49.860 --> 00:06:53.400
